race.comment: SPARKINGLY (11) resumes for a new yard with McDougall booked, and he's the go-to jockey around these parts. He's been off the scene for a long while but is certainly good enough and has won trials at Wyong and Newcastle in preparation. Some trust is required, but he looks all set to race boldly. TEYLU (5) won a CL1 here before the spell and resumed in good order with a 1.3L defeat at Wagga-Riverside as favourite. Keeps Owen and has plenty of scope for improvement. The local will be well-fancied to go one better. DITTERICH (3) grabbed a place at Wagga in stronger and was outgraded at Randwick prior. Led at Albury before that and was just knocked off in a 66. Has an inside barrier and a 2kg claim and has to be considered. ISCHYROS (7) resumes and won two on end before being outgraded at Randwick. He should be quick enough to clear the wide barrier and 2x winning rider Cahill stays aboard. Proven fresh and keep onside.
